2) Build the host GNU Radio spectrograph flowgraph

On the host, in GNU Radio Companion, make this chain:

TCP Source -> Interleaved Short To Complex -> Multiply Const -> QT GUI Frequency Sink
                                                 \-> QT GUI Waterfall Sink

Block settings

TCP Source

* Type: byte
* Num Channels: 1
* Address: 192.168.10.2
* Port: 5000
* Server: False
* Vectors: False

Interleaved Short To Complex

* Vector Input: No
* Scale Factor: leave default for now

Multiply Const

Use this to scale int16 IQ into roughly [-1, 1].

* Constant: 1.0 / 32768.0

QT GUI Frequency Sink

* Input type: complex
* Sample rate: same as stream, for example 250e3
* Center frequency: same as stream, for example 100e6

QT GUI Waterfall Sink

* Input type: complex
* Sample rate: same as stream
* Center frequency: same as stream

